By the rivers of Babylon, There we sat down and wept, When we remembered Zion. -- psalms 137:1
.
Upon the willows in the midst of it We hung our harps. -- psalms 137:2
.
For there our captors demanded of us songs, And our tormentors mirth, saying, "Sing us one of the songs of Zion." -- psalms 137:3
.
How can we sing the LORD'S song In a foreign land? -- psalms 137:4
.
If I forget you, O Jerusalem, May my right hand forget her skill. -- psalms 137:5
.
May my tongue cling to the roof of my mouth If I do not remember you, If I do not exalt Jerusalem Above my chief joy. -- psalms 137:6
.
